    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span12">
          <div class="hero-unit">
            <h1>PyCon Canada</h1>
            <br />
            <p>Building a Canadian Python community.</p>
            <p>Working together to showcase Canadian talent at PyCon in Montr√©al in 2014 and 2015.</p>
            <p>Can't make it to PyCon? There's still lots here for you! Learn new skills, share your ideas, or join the team helping to create and support PyCon Canada.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Contact Us</h2>
              <p>Don't be shy! Tell us your ideas around growing the Canadian Python community.</p>
              <p>twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/pyconca">@pyconca</a></p>
              <p>email: pyconca@gmail.com</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Join Us</h2>
              <p>Be a part of the fun! Developer or not, there are lots of ways you can help, from PyCon planning and coordination to developing and maintaining this web site. It's a great way to learn, share knowledge, and network with others across Canada.</p>
              <p>github: <a href="https://github.com/pyconca">https://github.com/pyconca</a></p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Sponsor Us</h2>
              <p>PyCon Canada is a volunteer effort. As we prepare for Python 2014, we'll need spaces to meet and practice presentations, and help to cover costs such as web hosting for the PyCon Canada site. Show your support, and we'll promote your company here!</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
          </div><!--/row-->
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Community</h2>
              <p>Python user groups in Canada. If your group isn't listed, just let us know!</p>
              <p>Want to start your own local user group? We can help. We're working to encourage safe places to practice public speaking, with PyCon 2014 in mind.</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Learn</h2>
              <p>Share what you know and learn from others. Improve your technical skills and presentation skills. Find out how to run effective meetings and events. Mentor others or find a mentor. Find schools that teach Python.</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span4">
              <h2>Career</h2>
              <p>Find Python jobs on the Canadian job board. Find out what companies in Canada use Python.</p>
              <p>Employers: send us your open Python positions and we'll post them here.</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
          </div><!--/row-->
        </div><!--/span-->

      </div><!--/row-->

